FAQWhat operating system does Surface Laptop run?Windows 10 S.What is Windows 10 S?Windows 10 S is a specific configuration of Windows 10 Pro that offers a familiar, productive Windows experience that’s streamlined for security and performance. By exclusively using apps in the Windows Store and ensuring that you browse safely with Microsoft Edge, Windows 10 S keeps you running fast and secure day in and day out.  Who is Windows 10 S designed for?Windows 10 S was inspired by students and teachers and it’s the best Windows ever for schools. It’s also a great choice for any Windows user looking for consistent performance and advanced security. By limiting apps to those in the Windows Store, Windows 10 S is ideal for people who have everything they need in the Windows Store and prefer the peace of mind that comes with removing the risk of downloading apps from other places.Can I switch to Windows 10 Pro? Switching to Windows 10 Pro is easy. If you want to do more, like run non-Store apps or use advanced features like remote desktop and BitLocker, you can easily switch at any time. • Simply go to the Settings Menu on your device, or visit the Windows Store to get started.• Making the switch is free until December 31, 2017. After December 31, the cost for Windows 10 Pro will be $49.






